author: julianfoad
msg: On the 'move-tracking-2' branch: Continue implementing top-level branching.
Change the Ev3-Ev1 conversion code towards converting all branches instead
of only those under a specified top-level branch. However, it still assumes
there is only one top-level branch. (Still to do: Map the top-level branches
to some hidden path-space.)
* subversion/include/private/svn_editor3e.h
(svn_editor3_in_memory): No longer take a top-level branch number as a
parameter.
* subversion/libsvn_delta/compat3e.c
(ev3_from_delta_baton_t): Remove the top-level branch number field.
(drive_changes_r): Process the hierarchy of nested branches within a given
top-level branch.
(drive_changes_branch): Take the top-level branch number as a parameter.
(editor3_sequence_point,
editor3_complete): Operate on all top-level branches.
(svn_editor3_in_memory): No longer take a top-level branch number as a
parameter.
* subversion/svnmover/svnmover.c
(wc_checkout): Adjust the call to svn_editor3_in_memory().
